    "Effective LR pacing uses skip-and-return: after roughly 1:30 to 2:00 of genuine stalling, mark the question, record a best guess so nothing is left blank, and move on to protect easier points later in the section. The sunk-cost instinct to keep grinding, and the opposite instinct to abandon the point entirely, both cost score.",
